Distribution. This species was originally described from the southwest coast of Madagascar (
Thomassin 1970
) but has been recorded from the Andaman Sea, Thailand (
Green 2002
) and it is now newly recorded for Oahu, Hawaii. This species seems to be one of the most abundant and widely distributed capitellids in Oahu and has been erroneously identified as
Notomastus tenuis
in unpublished reports (see e.g.
Ambrose et al. 2010
).
